name: NYDailyNews
text:
Anthony Rollo, a photo editor at the Daily News for more than 40 years, has died at 74.

Until 1991, the News called itself “New York’s Picture Newspaper,” and Rollo had a hand in most of the iconic covers from 9/11 to the blackout to infamous killers. 
https://t.co/3L6p48gsRS
